"* an induction start, in which آ§5 is set, and\n"
"* an induction step, in which the induction assumption آ§6 is available to "
"you.\n"
"\n"
"## Modifications in this game\n"
"\n"
"Outside of this game, آ§7 is called آ§8,\n"
"آ§9 is initially written as آ§10 and آ§11 as آ§12.\n"
"These terms are identical in definition, but occasionally need to be "
"explicitly rewritten with\n"
"آ§13 and آ§14."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `tauto`
#. آ§1: `generalize`
#. آ§2: `tauto`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The tactic آ§0 proves logical tautologies.\n"
"\n"
"# Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes the proof target must first be abstracted with آ§1 so that آ§2 "
"recognizes the tautology."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `rfl`
#. آ§1: `X = X`
#. آ§2: `rfl`
#. آ§3: `A = B`
#. آ§4: `A`
#. آ§5: `B`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The tactic آ§0 proves آ§1.  More precisely, آ§2 closes every proof target of "
"the form آ§3,\n"
"where آ§4 and آ§5 are identical in definition."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `simp`
#. آ§1: `mathlib`
#. آ§2: `@[simp]`
#. آ§3: `simp [h]`
#. آ§4: `h`
#. آ§5: `h`
#. آ§6: `simp [F]`
#. آ§7: `F`
#. آ§8: `simp only [h,f,g]`
#. آ§9: `h`
#. آ§10: `f`
#. آ§11: `g`
#. آ§12: `simp?`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The آ§0 tactic attempts to apply a large number of lemmas to simplify a given "
"expression.\n"
"(Technically, these are all lemmas in آ§1 that are marked with آ§2.)\n"
"\n"
"## Variants\n"
"\n"
"* آ§3 additionally uses the assumption آ§4 or the lemma آ§5 for simplification\n"
"* آ§6 additionally uses the definition of آ§7\n"
"* آ§8 exclusively uses the assumptions/lemmas/definitions آ§9, آ§10, and آ§11\n"
"* آ§12 shows you which lemmas were used"
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `constructor`
#. آ§1: `âٹ¢ A âˆ§ B`
#. آ§2: `âٹ¢ A`
#. آ§3: `âٹ¢ B`
#. آ§4: `âٹ¢ A â†” B`
#. آ§5: `âٹ¢ A â†’ B`
#. آ§6: `âٹ¢ B â†’ A`
#. آ§7: `obtain`
#. آ§8: `A âˆ¨ B`
#. آ§9: `left`
#. آ§10: `right`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The آ§0 tactic breaks down a proof goal into its constituent parts:\n"
"\n"
"| before | after                |\n"
"|:------------ |:----------------------- |\n"
"| آ§1    | آ§2 and آ§3         |\n"
"| آ§4    | آ§5 and آ§6 |\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"* You can break down an *assumption* into its components using آ§7.\n"
"* If you want to prove آ§8, you have to choose one side using آ§9 or آ§10."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `obtain`
#. آ§1: `h : A âˆ§ B`
#. آ§2: `obtain âں¨hâ‚پ, hâ‚‚âں© := h`
#. آ§3: `hâ‚پ : A`
#. آ§4: `hâ‚‚ : B`
#. آ§5: `h : A â†” B`
#. آ§6: `obtain âں¨hâ‚پ, hâ‚‚âں© := h`
#. آ§7: `hâ‚پ : A â†’ B`
#. آ§8: `hâ‚‚ : B â†’ A`
#. آ§9: `h : Nonempty X`
#. آ§10: `obtain âں¨xâں© := h`
#. آ§11: `x : X`
#. آ§12: `h : âˆƒ x : X, P x`
#. آ§13: `obtain âں¨x, hxâں© := h`
#. آ§14: `x : X`
#. آ§15: `hx : P x`
#. آ§16: `h : A âˆ¨ B`
#. آ§17: `obtain h \\| h := h`
#. آ§18: `h : A`
#. آ§19: `h : B`
#. آ§20: `\\<`
#. آ§21: `\\>`
#. آ§22: `âں¨_, _âں©`
#. آ§23: $(G, 0, +)$
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The آ§0 tactic breaks down an assumption into its individual parts.\n"
"\n"
"| before       | tactic                 | "
"after                                   |\n"
"|:------------------ |:--------------------- - "
"|:------------------------------------------ |\n"
"| آ§1        | آ§2 | آ§3 and آ§4                      |\n"
"| آ§5        | آ§6 | آ§7 and آ§8              |\n"
"| آ§9   | آ§10      | آ§11                                    |\n"
"| آ§12 | آ§13  | آ§14 and آ§15                     |\n"
"| آ§16        | آ§17   | a target with آ§18, a target with آ§19 |\n"
"\n"
"Type the brackets in the first four examples as آ§20 or آ§21.\n"
"Here, آ§22 is the *anonymous constructor*.\n"
"You can think of it as similar to the tuple notation in\n"
"â€œan abelian group is a tuple آ§23 such that ...â€‌."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `assumption`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The آ§0 tactic closes the proof if one of the assumptions corresponds exactly "
"to the proof target."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `let`
#. آ§1: `let x : â„• := 5 ^ 2`
#. آ§2: `let x := â€¦`
#. آ§3: `x`
#. آ§4: `simp only [x]`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The آ§0 tactic introduces a temporary definition, for example\n"
"آ§1.\n"
"\n"
"Once آ§2 defines a آ§3, you can use the definition later with آ§4."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `ring`
#. آ§1: `+, -, *, ^`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The آ§0 tactic proves equations with the operations آ§1 in semirings,\n"
"in particular in â„•, â„¤, â„ڑ, â„‌, â€¦   It works particularly well in commutative "
"rings."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `push_neg`
#. آ§1: `آ¬âˆ€ x, P x`
#. آ§2: `âˆƒ x, آ¬P x`
#. آ§3: `آ¬âˆƒ x, P x`
#. آ§4: `âˆ€ x, آ¬P x`
#. آ§5: `آ¬`
#. آ§6: ```
#.   آ¬ âˆ€ خµ, âˆƒ خ´, âˆ€ y, | x - y | < خ´ â†’ | f x - f y | < خµ
#. ```
#. آ§7: `push_neg`
#. آ§8: ```
#.   âˆƒ خµ, âˆ€ خ´, âˆƒ y, آ¬ (| x - y | < خ´ â†’ | f x - f y | < خµ)
#. ```
#. آ§9: `not_forall`
#. آ§10: `not_exists`
#. آ§11: `rw`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The آ§0 tactic pushes negation past quantifiers:\n"
"\n"
"| before       | after      |\n"
"|:------------ |:-------------|\n"
"| آ§1  | آ§2  |\n"
"| آ§3  | آ§4  |\n"
"\n"
"In nested expressions, it pushes the negation آ§5 as far to the right as "
"possible.\n"
"For example, the proof goal\n"
"آ§6\n"
"with آ§7\n"
"آ§8\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"The two lemmas آ§9 and آ§10 can be applied individually with آ§11."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: ```
#. f = g
#. ```
#. آ§1: `f g : X â†’ Y`
#. آ§2: `funext x`
#. آ§3: ```
#. f x = g x
#. ```
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"Two mappings with the same range and domain are equal if\n"
"they take the same values on all elements of the domain.\n"
"A proof goal of the form\n"
"آ§0\n"
"for mappings آ§1 is converted by آ§2\n"
"into the equation\n"
"آ§3."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: ```
#. A = B
#. ```
#. آ§1: `T`
#. آ§2: `A B : Set T`
#. آ§3: `ext x`
#. آ§4: ```
#. x âˆˆ A â†” x âˆˆ B
#. ```
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"Two subsets of a given set are equal if they have the same elements.\n"
"If the proof goal is\n"
"آ§0\n"
"for two subsets of آ§1 (i.e., for آ§2),\n"
"then آ§3 converts the proof goal into the equivalence\n"
"آ§4"
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `symm`
#. آ§1: `=`
#. آ§2: `â†”`
#. آ§3: `symm at h`
#. آ§4: `h`
#. آ§5: `h.symm`
#. آ§6: `symm at h`
#. آ§7: `h`
#. آ§8: `rw [â†گh]`
#. آ§9: ```
#.   symm at h
#.   rw [h]
#.   ```
#. آ§10: `rw [h.symm]`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0 (for â€œsymmetryâ€‌), you swap the sides of an equation (آ§1) or "
"equivalence (آ§2) in the proof target.\n"
"\n"
"## Variants\n"
"* آ§3 operates on the assumption آ§4 instead of the proof target\n"
"* آ§5 is the result of آ§6 and can be used like آ§7\n"
"\n"
"Each of the following three tactics or tactic sequences therefore has the "
"same effect:\n"
"* آ§8\n"
"* آ§9\n"
"* آ§10"
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `apply`
#. آ§1: `hAB : A â†’ B`
#. آ§2: `âٹ¢ B`
#. آ§3: `apply hAB`
#. آ§4: `âٹ¢ A`
#. آ§5: `h : A `
#. آ§6: `apply hAB at h`
#. آ§7: `h : B`
#. آ§8: `hAB`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you apply an implication آ§1:\n"
"\n"
"| before | tactic           | after |\n"
"|:------------ |:---------------- |:-------- |\n"
"| آ§2        | آ§3      | آ§4    |\n"
"| آ§5     | آ§6 | آ§7  |\n"
"\n"
"In both cases, the implication آ§8 can either be\n"
"given as an assumption or be an already known lemma."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `if â€¦ then â€¦ else`
#. آ§1: `fun x â†¦ if 0 â‰¤ x then x else -x`
#. آ§2: `h : A`
#. آ§3: `rw [if_pos h]`
#. آ§4: `if A then B else C`
#. آ§5: `B`
#. آ§6: `h : آ¬ A`
#. آ§7: `rw [if_neg h]`
#. آ§8: `if A then B else C`
#. آ§9: `C`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you can define mappings with two branches of definition.\n"
"\n"
"For example, آ§1 defines the absolute value function.\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"* If you have آ§2 as an assumption, you can use\n"
"آ§3 to reduce the expression آ§4 to آ§5.\n"
"* If you have آ§6 as an assumption, you can use\n"
"آ§7 to reduce the expression آ§8 to آ§9."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `generalize`
#. آ§1: `generalize h : a = b`
#. آ§2: `a`
#. آ§3: `b`
#. آ§4: `h : a = b`
#. آ§5: ```
#. Even x âˆ¨ آ¬Even x
#. ```
#. آ§6: ```
#. generalize h : (Even x) = A
#. ```
#. آ§7: ```
#. A âˆ¨ آ¬A
#. ```
#. آ§8: `tauto`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you can generalize a proof goal\n"
"in the hope that a higher level of abstraction will allow for a simpler "
"proof.\n"
"More precisely, آ§1 replaces all occurrences of آ§2 in the proof goal with آ§3\n"
"(and adds the assumption آ§4).\n"
"\n"
"## Example\n"
"\n"
"A goal of the form\n"
"آ§5\n"
"can be converted with\n"
"آ§6\n"
"into\n"
"آ§7\n"
"(and then simply proven with آ§8)."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `decide`
#. آ§1: `True`
#. آ§2: `Even 4`
#. آ§3: `2 â‰¤ 5`
#. آ§4: `4 â‰  6`
#. آ§5: `Prime 7`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you can prove statements that can be decided using a simple "
"algorithm.\n"
"These include, in particular, آ§1 and statements about concrete numbers such "
"as:\n"
"- آ§2\n"
"- آ§3\n"
"- آ§4\n"
"- آ§5"
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `unfold F`
#. آ§1: `F`
#. آ§2: `unfold F at h`
#. آ§3: `h`
#. آ§4: `unfold`
#. آ§5: `push_neg`
#. آ§6: `rw`
#. آ§7: `unfold F`
#. آ§8: `simp only [F]`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you can write out the definition آ§1 in the proof goal.\n"
"With آ§2, you do the same thing, but in the assumption آ§3.\n"
"\n"
"Although the proof goal or assumption before and after آ§4 are identical in "
"definition,\n"
"many tactics (e.g., آ§5 or آ§6) operate on a syntactic level;\n"
"they do not â€œsee through definitions.â€‌\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and Relatives\n"
"\n"
"The tactics آ§7 and آ§8 do practically the same thing."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `trans`
#. آ§1: `âٹ¢ A = C`
#. آ§2: `trans B`
#. آ§3: `âٹ¢ A = B`
#. آ§4: `âٹ¢ B = C`
#. آ§5: `âٹ¢ A â†” C`
#. آ§6: `trans B`
#. آ§7: `âٹ¢ A â†” B`
#. آ§8: `âٹ¢ B â†” C`
#. آ§9: `A = Bâ‚پ = Bâ‚‚ = Bâ‚ƒ â€¦ = C`
#. آ§10: `calc`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you insert an intermediate step into an equation or equivalence.\n"
"\n"
"| before | tactic    | after                |\n"
"|:------------ |:--------- |:----------------------- |\n"
"| آ§1    | آ§2 | آ§3 and آ§4 |\n"
"| آ§5    | آ§6 | آ§7 and آ§8 |\n"
"\n"
"Since you can repeat the tactic several times, it is suitable for\n"
"performing a â€œcalculationâ€‌ آ§9 step by step.\n"
"\n"
"(Outside of the game, however, the multi-line tactic آ§10 is better suited "
"for such calculations.)"
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `suffices h : P`
#. آ§1: `P`
#. آ§2: `P`
#. آ§3: `have h : P`
#. آ§4: `P`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you introduce a proof section in which you show\n"
"that the desired proof goal follows from آ§1.\n"
"Then you prove آ§2.\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"آ§3 works the same way, except that you must first prove آ§4 before you can\n"
"continue with the main proof."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `have h : P`
#. آ§1: `suffices h : P`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With آ§0, you introduce an intermediate result.\n"
"You must then prove this intermediate result\n"
"before you can continue with the actual proof.\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"آ§1 works in exactly the same way, except that you can continue with the main "
"proof first and\n"
"only have to prove your intermediate result at the very end."
msgstr ""

#. آ§0: `specialize h aâ‚پ aâ‚‚`
#. آ§1: `have h := h aâ‚پ aâ‚‚`
#. آ§2: `h : âˆ€ mâ‚پ mâ‚‚, P mâ‚پ mâ‚‚`
